transliteration: Kar(i) Jag Mo Eh Bhaant Akhaaraa|| Navam Vataar Bisan Im Dhaaraa||
translation: In this way, Vishnu manifested for the ninth time in order to enact the wonderful play.

transliteration: Ab Barno Dasmo Avtaaraa|| Sant Janaa Kaa Praan Adhaaraa||35||
translation: Now I describe the tenth incarnation, who is the support of the life-breath of the saints.35.

transliteration: It(i) Sribachitra Naatake Navmo Avtaar Kathanan|| Parasraam Avtaar||9|| Samaaptam Sat(u) Soubham Sat(u)||
translation: End of the description of the ninth incarnation PARASHURAMA in BACHITTAR NATAK.9.
Now begins the description of Brahma Incarnation:
Let Sri Bhagauti Ji (The Primal Lord) be helpful.

transliteration: Ab Ouchro Mai Kathaa Chiraanee|| Jim Oupjyo Brahmaasur Ghaanee||
translation: Now I describe that ancient story as to how the knowledgeable Brahma was bron.

transliteration: Chaturaanan Agh Oghan Hartaa|| Oupjyo Sakal Sristtee Ko Kartaa||1||
translation: The four-headed Brahma was born as the destroyer of sins and the creator of all the universe.1.

gurmukhi: jb jb byd nws hoie jwhI ] qb qb pun bHmw pRgtwhI ]
transliteration: Jab Jab Bed Naas Hoe Jaahee|| Tab Tab Poun Brahmaa Pragtaahee||
translation: Whenever the knowledge of Vedas is destroyed, Brahma is then manifested.

transliteration: Taa Te Bisan Brahm Bap(u) Dharaa|| Chaturaanan Kar Jagad Ouchraa||2||
translation: For this purpose Vishnu manifested himself ad Brahma and he was known as “Chaturanan” (four-faced) in the world.2.

gurmukhi: jb hI ibsn bHm bpu Drw ] qb sB byd pRcur jg krw ]
transliteration: Jab Hibisan Brahm Bap(u) Dharaa|| Tab Sabh Bed Prachur Jag Karaa||
translation: When Vishnu manifested himself as Brahma, he propagated the doctrines of the Vedas in the world.
